--- !u!114 &1150804215
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1150804212}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1d4aca9d43172344fba787b7c53d611f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  storyLines:
  - 'The puzzle was hard wasn''t it? or was it? '
  - Did you just flick the switches and just hope that one of the opens? If you did,
    you might regret it later.
  - When you flick the NOT Gate switch at the top you the switch will turn off, but
    since it's a NOT Gate, it will return True. The switch at the right triggers
    the other input for the OR Gate. Because it was a OR Gate, either of the two
    that returned true will return True to the AND Gate that will open the door.
  - 'The bottom NOT Gate switch will turn off when you flick it, but since it''s
    a NOT Gate it will return True, and since the NOT Gate also goes through another
    NOT Gate, the boolean value that will be returned to the follwong AND Gate is
    False. '
  - The bottom AND Gate Switches when flicked to both ON the AND Gate will return
    true to the NOT Gate, but since it's a NOT Gate, the resulting boolean value
    is False. The following AND Gate will return False, since both values that was
    returned was False, the resulting value will be Flase, but there's a NOT Gate
    after the AND gate, resulting in turning the boolean value into TRUE.
  - The last step is adding up all the values, since the the one responsible for
    opening the door is an AND Gate, it will need both values from its inputs to
    be True. As explaied before, the door opened becasue the AND Gate succesfully
    recieve both True values.
  - The last stage to deem you worthy is waiting ahead...good luck.
